  "execution_target": "cpp",
  "optimization_notes": "Root cause is a physical-plan/hardware mismatch (Category B/C): the prior path still depends on very large triple posting structures whose entry arrays exceed LLC and add high load/probe overhead relative to useful output work. This plan removes triple-index dependency from the hot path, uses sub.fy=2023 as an early semi-join to prune pre stmt postings, builds a cache-resident runtime hash on filtered pre triples, then probes it from num adsh postings while applying USD and non-null checks before aggregation; it also defers wide string decoding to final top-k output so data loading and random access are reduced.",
